Taraba State Governor, Arc Darius Dickson Ishaku has extended his warm facilitation to Governor Obaseki on his well-deserved victory in the just concluded Edo State gubernatorial election. A statement by his media aide, Bala Dan Abu described Obaseki‘s victory as an acknowledgement of good job the governor had rendered to the people of the state in his first tenure. Governor Ishaku also commended the the Independent National Electoral Commission INEC,  for providing the level playing field that led to  the credible results delivered in the election. He commended the entire Edo people for demonstrating a lot of maturity by their peaceful conduct during and after the elections and by so  doing disappointing those who had predicted that Edo State would be  engulfed by crisis during the exercise.